Crude Oil Falls a Fourth Day After Earthquake in Japan Shuts Refineries

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   S c h m o l l i n g e r   a n d   Y e e   K a i   P i n
-- 
2011-03-11T07:24:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/crude-oil-falls-a-fourth-day-after-earthquake-in-japan-shuts-refineries.html
Oil fell for a fourth day in  New
York  after an 8.8-magnitude earthquake struck off the coast of
northern Japan, shutting refineries.  Crude for April delivery tumbled as much as $1.83, or 1.8
percent, to $100.87 a barrel in electronic trading on the  New
York Mercantile Exchange . It was at $101.12 at 3:22 p.m.
Singapore time. Brent oil for April settlement on the London-
based ICE Futures Europe exchange dropped as much as $2.60, or
2.3 percent, to $112.83 a barrel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Schmollinger in Singapore at 
 christian.s@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
